Standard solution of levodopa (300μM) was used for pH optimization in levodopa determination by RTIL-GQDs/CPE employing cyclic voltammetry (CV) (Fig. 2
                         inset) [12]. It was observed that best electrochemical oxidation current obtained at pH=7.0 and also with increasing pH value, the oxidation peak potential shifted towards less positive values, which proposing the involvement of protons in the reaction. Fig. 2 shows the plot of peak potential vs. pH for levodopa in the pH range of 5.0–8.0. As can be seen, a slope of −0.050V was obtained for levodopa which confirmed equal number of electrons and protons in electro-oxidation of levodopa (Scheme 1
                        ).
